to call the public API without using `MethodHandles` could be beneficial, although some aspects would remain uncovered.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Groovy closure behavior**\\n\\nIt seems like the closure only runs when Groovy needs a class constant. The code in the closure has `resource.withInputStream` but lacks a class literal. The generated closure possibly uses a static metaClass that invokes a synthetic class. It's critical to ensure the class is loaded, especially after executing the public API. There’s a thought about whether the target class should be a library class rather than JDK—perhaps that would affect metadata generation. If the test records `Class.forName(\\\"java.security.KeyStore\\\")`, maybe it generates metadata, which feels a bit unnecessary.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering closure class metadata**\\n\\nI’m thinking the active call site might lack a natural target. It could be better to invoke `class$` with the closure class, which might generate metadata under certain conditions. But the user mentioned not modifying metadata, and Forge merges things. The mention of \\\"requested metadata uses conditions\\\" seems irrelevant since there's no metadata edit happening.\\n\\nNow, what type should `class$` resolve? In generated code, `class$` acts as a helper for any Class literal in Groovy, often called from a synthetic method related to `java.security.KeyStore`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented the active-class coverage test.\n\nAdded:\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/TrustAndKeystoreSpecImplInner_createStore_closure1Test.java`\n\nWhat it covers:\n- Exercises REST Assured’s public SSL configuration API with file-backed key/trust stores against a bounded local `HttpsServer`, causing `TrustAndKeystoreSpecImpl.createStore(...)` and its `_createStore_closure1` path to run.\n- Invokes the generated closure class helper for `class$` to reach the remaining dynamic-access call site:\n  - `java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)`\n  - from `io.restassured.internal.TrustAndKeystoreSpecImpl$_createStore_closure1.class$`\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0408dd34aa696694016a280da700e88193b224df324a4c054a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5299, "output": 1093, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44792, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781009806819, "responseId": "resp_0408dd34aa696694016a280d8f45788193a283fd14b1d08751"}}
