ugh normal library execution.\n\nImportant finding:\n- The remaining reported call site is `TrustAndKeystoreSpecImpl$_createStore_closure1.class$`.\n- In the compiled artifact this is an `ACC_SYNTHETIC` Groovy-generated helper with no source line number and it is not called by the normal public SSL store-loading path.\n- The dynamic-access coverage logic marks line-less call sites as uncovered, so this specific synthetic `class$` site does not appear coverable via supported public API behavior. Directly forcing it with method handles/reflection did not improve the report and is not an appropriate supported-behavior test path.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0408dd34aa696694016a280f0a0d2c8193aefb3e82d806d862\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1233, "output": 968, "cacheRead": 67584, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 69785, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781010165451, "responseId": "resp_0408dd34aa696694016a280ef610f88193a809d0e853002cd2"}}
